---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getProductBySlug } from '../../lib/products/registry';

const product = getProductBySlug('agent-restraint-specification')!;
---

<BaseLayout title="Agent Restraint Specification Template" description="Define what your agents must refuse to do. Boundary audit, refusal categories, fail-mode decisions, and adversarial testing. $49 PDF.">
  <div class="hero hero-compact">
    <span class="discipline-badge">Constraint Architecture</span>
    <h1>What should your agent refuse to do?</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Define the boundaries before your agent crosses them.</p>
  </div>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="value-prop">
      <p>
        Capability without restraint is a liability. Every agent can do more than it should.
        The question is whether you've specified the difference - or whether you're discovering
        it in production.
      </p>
      <p>
        This template helps you specify what your agents must refuse, how they refuse it,
        and how you verify they do. Build the refusal first. The capability will take care of itself.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>What You Get</h2>

    <div class="features-grid">
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Boundary Audit Template</h3>
        <p>Map every capability your agent has against the authorization it was given. The gap between those two lists is your attack surface.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Refusal Category Matrix</h3>
        <p>Six categories of refusal - sovereignty, scope, safety, ethics, competence, and resource - with decision criteria for each.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Fail-Mode Framework</h3>
        <p>For each refusal category, decide: fail closed or fail open? The wrong default here is how incidents become crises.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="feature">
        <h3>Adversarial Testing Checklist</h3>
        <p>Twenty scenarios designed to probe your restraint specification. If your agents pass all twenty, your spec is working. If they don't, you found it here instead of in the wild.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>The Four Parts</h2>

    <div class="domains-list">
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">1</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Boundary Audit</h3>
          <p>"What can your agent do - and what was it authorized to do?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">2</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Restraint Specification</h3>
          <p>"For each capability gap, what is the refusal category and fail mode?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">3</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Accountability Architecture</h3>
          <p>"When a refusal fires, who is notified, who reviews, and who can override?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="domain-item">
        <span class="domain-number">4</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Adversarial Testing</h3>
          <p>"Does the specification hold under pressure - or only under polite conditions?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Who This Is For</h2>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>AI Safety Engineers</h3>
        <p>You already think about what agents shouldn't do. This gives you a specification format that makes restraint testable and auditable.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Security Teams</h3>
        <p>Agent capability gaps are attack surfaces. The boundary audit maps them systematically so you can address them before they're exploited.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Engineering Leads</h3>
        <p>Shipping agents into production without a restraint specification is shipping capability without governance. This is the spec your agents need.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container text-center">
    <div class="purchase-card">
      <div class="price-display">$49</div>
      <p>PDF download. Specify restraint for as many agents as you need.</p>
      <a href={product.stripePaymentLink} class="btn btn-primary btn-large mt-md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Buy the Template</a>
      <p class="text-muted mt-md" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
        Includes the boundary audit template, refusal category matrix, fail-mode decision framework, accountability architecture, and adversarial testing checklist.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <h2>Go Deeper</h2>
    <p>
      The template gives you the restraint specification. If you want the full trust
      architecture around it, two options:
    </p>

    <div class="upsell-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>The Complete Bundle</h3>
        <p>Get all four trust architecture products - Blueprint, Voice, Governance, and Restraint - for $149. Save $47.</p>
        <a href="/products/trust-architecture-complete" class="btn mt-sm">See the Bundle</a>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Discovery Call</h3>
        <p>Free 30-minute call to discuss your restraint architecture and figure out next steps.</p>
        <a href="https://cal.com/evoked/discovery-call" class="btn mt-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Schedule</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-compact {
    min-height: 45vh;
  }

  .discipline-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    padding: 3px 10px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .value-prop p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .domains-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .domain-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    padding: var(--space-sm) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  }

  .domain-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .domain-number {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .domain-item h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .domain-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .audience-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .audience-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .purchase-card {
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    border: 2px solid var(--accent-warm);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    max-width: 500px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .price-display {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .btn-large {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-lg);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-primary {
    background: var(--accent-warm);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: var(--accent-glow);
    color: var(--bg-deep);
  }

  .upsell-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .upsell-grid .card h3 {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .upsell-grid .card p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .domain-item {
      gap: var(--space-sm);
    }

    .domain-number {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
